We have been working on a robust understanding of marriage.

<<<
For the man who does not love his wife but divorces her, says the LORD, the God of Israel, covers his garment with violence, says the LORD of hosts. So guard yourselves in your spirit, and do not be faithless."
<<<
Malachi 2:16

David had Solomon, through Solomon, blessings. General peace of having one particular purpose of being able to build the temple of God. So Solomon has a son called Rehoboam who was not so smart. Was very foolish. The kingdom was divided into Northern Kingdom and Southern Kingdom. Northern Kingdom had 10 kingdoms while 2 in the Southern Kingdom.

There were occasionally good kings but otherwise they are always a mess. God proves king after king after king that things are a mess.

His kingdom will be forever. Your sins will be no more. In the drama of the Old Testament, you are anticipating whether or not there will be a promised. You see the Kingdom spiraling out of control. Throughout this entire time, God is trying to woo the Kingdom.

God does this generation after generation about 700 years. Patient, patient, patient.

Judah is warned about impending exile but God makes a promise through the promise of Jacob. At the end of the 70 years, Ezra and Nehemiah come in.

Ezra and Nehemiah are dealing with marriage with foreign women to prevent their hearts from being taken away. The nation was re-established, temple rebuilt, but now they are remarrying once more.

Blessing is not coming into the land. They go and they ask God why they are being treated like this. Why are they so hard? Look at their sinfulness.

Malachi 2:10-16

Everything has to be staked on His faithfulness not ours.

