Because the LORD was witness between you and the wife of your youth, to whom you have been faithless, though she is your companion and your wife by covenant.
<<<
Malachi 2:14

The commandment of the Scripture is for husbands to act as husbands. We often us work as an excuse. Don't you understand this is what God is trying to get us to understand. You are dealing treacherously the wife of your youth though she was a companion to you. She is not your servant, she is your friend.

"In this case, the wife was a faithful witness to her husband. To grow old together, to bear for her husband. But yet he had decided to cast her aside."

In a sense God says that this is a covenant that you have made, buddy. No one has forced you to make this covenant.

One truth that blends through out Scripture, that is really helpful, is that God is a protector of the weak. You have words like affliction, oppression, abuse, etc.

The Lord is a stronghold for the oppressed. A stronghold for times of trouble.

