Matthew 5:31-32

<<<
He said to them, "Because of your hardness of heart Moses allowed you to divorce your wives, but from the beginning it was not so. And I say to you: whoever divorces his wife, except for sexual immorality, and marries another, commits adultery."
<<<
Matthew 19:8-9

Some respectable teachers say the following: the reason there is an exception clause in Matthew is probably because of the account to birth. That is why Matthew adds these clauses in order to show that Joseph was going to send Mary away. But the problem is it doesn't fit the context. Genesis 1 and 2, Adam and Eve were not betrothed. Jesus was explaining what was going on in the context of marriage.

Deuteronomy 24 is not talking about betrothal either. Jesus was clearly talking about marriage. To limit to that word to pronae was not how it was used.

Yes, adultery is treated as a particularly evil sexual sin. Sometimes pornae is a synonym for adultery. The discussion was over Deuteronomy 24.

Leviticus 20:10 - Consequences of adultery is death. Writing a certificate of divorce and sending he away.

In accordance to the law of Moses, there are some sexual sins that may lead to divorce. Moses permitted writing a certificate of divorce and putting them away.

Jesus does not use the same word in Matthew 19 from Matthew 5. Thus today we see that the word with pornae is for general words. That is why God gives the church various counseling situations.

Jeremiah 3:1-5

Then God tells Josiah (Jeremiah 3:6-10) that Judah did not fear the Lord. Time and time again, God says that Israel and Judah had looked to whores.

<<<
Thus says the LORD: "Where is your mother's certificate of divorce, with which I sent her away? Or which of my creditors is it to whom I have sold you? Behold, for your iniquities you were sold, and for your transgressions your mother was sent away.
<<<
Isaiah 50

So eventually God does the unthinkable and writes a certificate of divorce. But God says things are difficult right now but things will be better. No longer does God have to tell His neighbor to know the Lord. The sins that ripped you apart from me will be no longer. Ezekiel 36. The problem is in our hearts. The only one who can change our hearts.

In the meantime, God stands divorce. For those who argue that divorce is inconsistent with God's Word, how do you describe this? That our God stands divorced for the time being. Marriage is supposed to be the picture of the Gospel. This is why Jesus came to win Him to Himself. It isn't because are so faithful and beautiful and so lovely. It is because He is loved.

While we were filthy in our sins and Christ died for us.

The Old Testament was full of messy marriages. Yet throughout Scripture, very few talked about divorces. That as sinful as people were, they had a sense that God hates divorce. We will rely on Him in faith to work through it and work through it. Just because a marriage can end in divorce does not mean that it should or that it must. Please be praying for the leaders of this church as we counsel difficult situations.